<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,1000,1907,1932]" pageId="78" pageNumber="355">Current name</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="E. Geoffroy, 1804" authorityName="E. Geoffroy" authorityYear="1804" box="[1012,1462,1908,1934]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Hydromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="78" pageNumber="355" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysogaster">
<emphasis box="[1012,1265,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="355">Hydromys chrysogaster</emphasis>
É. 
<bibRefCitation author="Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire, E" box="[1298,1462,1908,1932]" pageId="78" pageNumber="355" pagination="353 - 354" refId="ref130173" refString="Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire, E. 1804. Note sur un nouveau genre de mammiferes, de l'ordre des rongeurs, sous le nom d'Hydromys. Bulletin des sciences par la Societe Philomathique de Paris 3 (93): 353 - 354 [misprinted as 253 - 254]." type="journal article" year="1804">Geoffroy, 1804</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; following Jackson &amp; Groves, 2015). Taxonomic status unresolved: a detailed taxonomic review of the extensive variation within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="E. Geoffroy" authorityYear="1804" box="[1012,1265,1996,2020]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Hydromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="78" pageNumber="355" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysogaster">
<emphasis box="[1012,1265,1996,2020]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="355">Hydromys chrysogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is needed, and two species could be present in south-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[552,650,1618,1642]" name="Australia" pageId="79" pageNumber="356">Australia</collectingCountry>
(Jackson &amp; Groves, 2015).
</paragraph>
